how do you handle a boss who is difficult to work with but is only trying to help you become a better person a boss who cares about you and gives constructive criticism but has some undesirable traits of his own such as making condescending remarks to point out a subordinate's deficiencies getting to work late like around am asking how is it going every minutes or so do you accept him for who he is and try to adapt or say something i think it's good that he's brutally honest rather than not saying anything at all but something needs to change because the worker is getting wrecked emotionally and physically due to long hours speak with your boss privately and explain to him that while you appreciate his leadership and his kindness towards you it would be better if he could express himself in a less condescending manner when trying to help you improve as an employee remain as calm as possible and speak in a manner that does not offend or hurt your boss's feelings because it seems that he is really a good guy who has your best interests at heart remember to be patient as he makes the effort to change because it won't happen immediately just express yourself honestly and respectfully i wish you well Transactional analysis Social rule Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Scientology beliefs and practices Personality psychology Theory of conduct Asperger syndrome Time Out of Mind A Course In Miracles Hypoglycemia Tai Chi Chuan Antisocial personality disorder Labour economics Political correctness Health insurance Borderline personality disorder Ethics Leviathan (book) Unemployment Peer review Alcoholics Anonymous Psychoanalysis Dualism (philosophy of mind) Internet troll Spanking Buffy Summers Hierarchy Infantilism Sydney Riot of 1879 Past teachings of Prem Rawat Episodes of Lost (Season 2) Religious Society of Friends Explosive material Singlish Culture Pok__mon Live! Narcissism Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel Leadership Criticisms of Charismatic and Pentecos